<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-14127] The destination File gets override even if you set the option fileExist to Append  </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-14127</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi, I&apos;m trying to append the content of a series of text files to another file with file-component using fileExist=Append but the destination file acts like it&apos;s been overrided!&lt;br/&gt;
Here&apos;s how I did it:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;from(&quot;file:G:/high&quot;).to(&quot;file:G:/test?fileName=test.txt&amp;amp;fileExist=Append&quot;);&lt;/p&gt;</description>
